    "summary": {
        "en": [
            "Heinrich Glück studied art history at the University of Vienna, where he received his doctorate in 1914 under Joseph Strzygowski. In 1919, he qualified as a university lecturer in the art history of the Orient, the Middle Ages, and the modern era, and in 1923 he was appointed associate professor. From 1928, he was curator at the Austrian Museum of Art and Industry."
        ]
    },
